## 5. Provider Architecture Details

**File:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775507066143-lyfyz5/contributing/provider-architecture.md`

### Layered Architecture

```
AI Functions (ai package)
    ↓
Shared Utilities (@ai-sdk/provider-utils)
    ↓
Provider Implementations (@ai-sdk/<provider>)
    ↓
Specifications (@ai-sdk/provider)
    ↓
External APIs (OpenAI, Google, etc.)
```

### Provider Registration Pattern

From `OpenAI` example at `/packages/openai/src/openai-provider.ts`:

```typescript
export interface OpenAIProvider extends ProviderV3 {
  (modelId: OpenAIResponsesModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  languageModel(modelId: OpenAIResponsesModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  chat(modelId: OpenAIChatModelId): LanguageModelV3;
  image(modelId: OpenAIImageModelId): ImageModelV3;
  imageModel(modelId: OpenAIImageModelId): ImageModelV3;
  embedding(modelId: OpenAIEmbeddingModelId): EmbeddingModelV3;
  embeddingModel(modelId: OpenAIEmbeddingModelId): EmbeddingModelV3;
  // ... more methods
}

export function createOpenAI(options: OpenAIProviderSettings = {}): OpenAIProvider {
  const provider = function (modelId: OpenAIResponsesModelId) {
    return createLanguageModel(modelId);
  };

  provider.specificationVersion = 'v3' as const;
  provider.languageModel = createLanguageModel;
  provider.image = createImageModel;
  provider.imageModel = createImageModel;
  // ... assign all model methods

  return provider as OpenAIProvider;
}
```

### Configuration Passing Pattern

Model constructors receive a config object with:
- `provider`: string (namespaced, e.g., `"openai.image"`)
- `url`: function that builds API URLs
- `headers`: function that returns request headers
- `fetch`: optional custom fetch implementation
- `_internal`: optional internal utilities (date provider, etc.)

Example from OpenAIImageModel:
```typescript
const createImageModel = (modelId: OpenAIImageModelId) =>
  new OpenAIImageModel(modelId, {
    provider: `${providerName}.image`,
    url: ({ path }) => `${baseURL}${path}`,
    headers: getHeaders,
    fetch: options.fetch,
  });
```

